%N A007631 Number of solutions to non-attacking reflecting queens problem.
%C A007631 a(n) is the number of ways to pair the natural numbers from 1 to n with those between n+1 and 2*n into n pairs (xi,yi) such that the 2*n numbers yi+xi and yi-xi are all different. - _Michel Marcus_,  Apr 27 2016 [Corrected by _Martin Fuller_, Nov 29 2025]
